<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1917-05-24T18:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1917-05-24T18:00:00-05:00" n="321" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d321">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">710.11/343a: Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the Ambassador in Brazil</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Morgan</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1917-05-24T18:00:00-05:00">
                                    <hi rend="italic">May 24, 1917—6 p. m.</hi>
                                </date>
                            </dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>Department is not sending to you the text of the Pan American treaty
                            which you were informed prior to your departure from the United States
                            would be cabled to you, as it does not desire you to take up this
                            question with the Government of Brazil at this time.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Lansing</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                </body></text></TEI>